    "discriminators": [
     "A flag, cape, sail or parachute: a quasi-periodic train of soft whip-cracks. The diagnostic pair is a moderate onset_rate (roughly 1-8 whips per second) with a HIGH onset_periodicity — that periodicity is exactly what UCS is naming when it splits FLAP out of CLOTH-MOVEMENT.",
     "Each whip is a dull, damped, mid-band transient with no ring — the cloth signature, unlike PAPER-FLUTTER's bright stochastic crackle.",
     "Not a rhythmic METAL sound: no partials, no sustain, and a decay under ~50 ms."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "CLOTHMvmt",
     "PAPRFltr",
     "CLOTHImpt"
    ]
   }
