    "discriminators": [
     "Cloth impact: soft-to-moderate attack, low crest relative to hard materials, and a decay of about 25 ms.",
     "The deadest material on the impedance axis: no ring at all, soft attack, mid-low centroid — the anti-METAL, and softer than any WOOD-IMPACT.",
     "A jacket thrown to the floor or a wet-towel snap: a soft, dull thump with the fastest decay and the lowest level of any material here. Cloth is the deadest thing in the taxonomy — no ring, low crest, mid-low centroid.",
     "This is the explicit anti-METAL: where METAL-IMPACT has a long inharmonic ring, cloth has none at all, and even a WOOD-IMPACT thud is sharper and louder."
    ],
