    "discriminators": [
     "Cloth movement: a sustained-but-eventful drag/rustle bed — many low-level micro-onsets, no single dominant transient, sustain_ratio well above IMPACT.",
     "Longer and far less front-loaded than the same material's IMPACT; less continuous and less high-centroid than its FRICTION.",
     "Cloth rustle or 'zuzz': broadband soft noise, heavily damped, mid-to-low centroid, very low level. The classic dead-material texture.",
     "Against PAPER-HANDLE: paper crumple is 4-6x brighter with a far higher onset_rate; cloth rustle smears into a soft noise bed with no distinct micro-cracks.",
     "Against LEATHER-MOVEMENT: leather is stiffer, so it produces occasional creak partials; cloth stays purely stochastic with harmonicity near zero.",
     "UCS routes flapping to CLOTH-FLAP: if the onset train is quasi-periodic, prefer that sibling."
    ],
